premise_source_doc_sentence: There is hereby adopted as the official colored seal of the State of South Dakota , a reproduction of the seal , described in article XXI , section 1 of the Constitution of the State of South Dakota , and made in conformity therewith but whose proportions and colored detail are set out specifically in accord with an original painting of the great seal produced by John G. Moisan of Fort Pierre and shall be the basis for all reproductions of the great seal of the State of South Dakota .
The seal-making device is also referred to as the seal matrix or die ; the imprint it creates as the seal impression  (  or , more rarely , the sealing  )  .
